Package lib.lists

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayIterator<T>
    A generic iterator for an array that allows traversal over the array's elements.
    ArrayList<T>
    ArrayList is an abstract base class that provides a generic implementation of a dynamic array-based list data structure.
    ArrayOrderedList<T>
    ArrayOrderedList represents an array-based implementation of an ordered list where elements are automatically arranged in their natural order as defined by their Comparable interface.
    ArrayUnorderedList<T>
    The ArrayUnorderedList class represents an implementation of an unordered list using an array as the underlying data structure.
    CircularDoubleLinkedList<T>
    A generic circular doubly linked list implementation that provides various operations to manage elements of the list.
    DoubleLinkedListIterator<T>
    Iterator implementation for a doubly linked list.
    DoubleLinkedOrderedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The DoubleLinkedOrderedList class represents a doubly linked ordered list.
    DoubleLinkedUnorderedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>  
    DoublyLinkedList<T>  
    LinkedList<T>  
    LinkedList.LinearNode<T>
    Represents a node in a linked data structure where each node contains an element and a reference to the next node in the sequence.
    LinkedOrderedList<T>  
    LinkedUnorderedList<T>
